    const y = ((clientY - rect.top) / rect.height) * 100;

    light.style.setProperty('--cursor-x', `${x}%`);
    light.style.setProperty('--cursor-y', `${y}%`);
    light.style.setProperty('--cursor-opacity', '1');
}, []);

const handleAmbientLeave = useCallback(() => {
    const light = ambientLightRef.current;
    if (light) {
        light.style.setProperty('--cursor-opacity', '0');
    }
}, []);
```

4. Attach these to the `.stageShell` div:
```jsx
<div
    ref={shellRef}
    className={...}
    onMouseMove={handleAmbientMove}
    onMouseLeave={handleAmbientLeave}
    onTouchMove={handleAmbientMove}
    onTouchEnd={handleAmbientLeave}
>
```

**Performance:** No React re-renders. Direct DOM style manipulation on a non-Konva element. The radial gradient is GPU-composited. This will not affect the 60fps target.

**Mobile consideration:** On touch devices, the light follows the finger during drag. On touch-end it fades out via the CSS transition. This feels natural -- like lifting a lamp off the paper.

